      <h2>Setup</h2>

      <div class="warning">
        <strong>The machine weighs 495 lbs (224 kg).</strong> Ensure you have enough people to handle it safely. If you have any doubt, seek professional assistance.
      </div>

      <h3>Placement &amp; Unboxing</h3>
      <p>The machine will likely be delivered by a third-party service. Inspect the packaging, invoice, and shipping documents before the driver leaves. All shipping damage must be noted upon delivery. Save all packaging until you are satisfied with the machine.</p>
      <p>Placement guidelines:</p>
      <ol>
        <li>Sufficient area at the front for comfortable work.</li>
        <li>Sufficient area at the back for adjustments and maintenance.</li>
        <li>Adequate lighting.</li>
        <li>Solid, flat floor (preferably concrete).</li>
        <li>Close to power source and dust collection.</li>
        <li>Allow area for storage of blanks, finished products, and tools.</li>
      </ol>

      <p>The jointer comes packed in two crates. A forklift may be required.</p>
      <div class="figure">
        <img src="/manuals/laguna-jx8/p15_01.jpg" alt="Crated JX8 jointer ready for unboxing" />
        <figcaption>Crated machine</figcaption>
      </div>
      <ol>
        <li>Remove the stand crate from the pallet and place on the floor.</li>
        <li>Cut banding and open crate. Remove the stand.</li>
        <li>Install leveling feet or casters into the stand (may be factory installed), or place on a mobile base.</li>
        <li>Remove the top covering the jointer body (typically screwed or nailed).</li>
        <li>Remove the two ends of the crate.</li>
        <li>Remove excess packing and crating material.</li>
        <li>Remove cardboard or foam packing material.</li>
        <li>Verify all parts are present and in good condition using the inventory list.</li>
      </ol>

      <h3>Inventory List</h3>
