      <h2>Assembly</h2>

      <h3>Machine Preparation</h3>
      <ol>
        <li>If equipped with four wheels (model dependent), two on the infeed side are locking style. Lock them by turning the thumbscrew clockwise before operation. Loosen when moving the jointer.
          <div class="figure">
            <img src="/manuals/laguna-jx8/p17_00.jpg" alt="JX8 wheel locks — thumbscrew detail" />
            <figcaption>Wheel locks</figcaption>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>Position the jointer body on the stand with the cutterhead pulley directly above and on the same side as the motor pulley. Have help lifting or use a forklift.
          <div class="figure">
            <img src="/manuals/laguna-jx8/p18_01.png" alt="Assembling jointer body onto stand" />
            <figcaption>Assembling the jointer</figcaption>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>Insert three bolts (with lock washer and flat washer) into each hole of the jointer body. Thread each bolt into the mating nut (factory secured) of the stand.</li>
        <li>Use a wrench to tighten each bolt.</li>
      </ol>

      <div class="warning">
        <strong>Be careful when working near the cutterhead &mdash; the knives are very sharp!</strong>
      </div>

      <h3>Drive Belt Installation</h3>
      <ol>
        <li>Attach the drive belt between the cutterhead pulley and motor pulley. Reach into the dust chute or cabinet base and use a wrench to loosen the four bolts holding the motor to the mounting bracket.</li>
        <li>Align the pulleys using the slotted holes on the motor mounting bracket.</li>
        <li>Raise the motor as high as possible and mount the belt on both pulleys. Allow the motor to lower and create tension.</li>
        <li>Pull down on the motor to achieve the desired belt tension. Correct tension is when the belt can be deflected approximately 1/2" (1/4" each side) at center using light finger pressure.
          <div class="figure">
            <img src="/manuals/laguna-jx8/p18_02.png" alt="Belt tension — 1/2 inch deflection at center" />
            <figcaption>Belt tension: 1/2" (1/4" each side of belt)</figcaption>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>Tighten the four motor mounting bolts.</li>
        <li>Install the pulley cover using four 1/4-20 &times; 1/2" bolts through the cover and into the base.</li>
      </ol>

      <h3>Surface Preparation</h3>
      <p>Clean all rust-protected surfaces with a commercial degreaser. Do not use acetone, gasoline, lacquer thinner, or cleaners that could damage paint. Coat cleaned surfaces with WD-40 or Teflon-based lubricant.</p>

      <h3>Power Supply</h3>
      <p>Circuit size: 220V, 1-Phase, 15 Amp minimum. Never replace a circuit breaker with one of higher amperage without consulting a qualified electrician.</p>
      <p>Plug the power cord into a 20 Amp, 220V, Single Phase, dedicated circuit.</p>

      <div class="danger">
        <strong>Make certain the receptacle is properly grounded.</strong> If you are not sure, have a qualified electrician check it. The completed installation must conform to the National Electric Code and all local codes.
      </div>

      <h2>Cutterhead &amp; Knife Inserts</h2>

      <div class="figure">
        <img src="/manuals/laguna-jx8/p26_01.jpg" alt="ShearTec II cutterhead with carbide inserts" />
        <figcaption>ShearTec II Cutterhead</figcaption>
      </div>
      <div class="figure">
        <img src="/manuals/laguna-jx8/p26_02.jpg" alt="Holding cutterhead with Torx driver during knife rotation" />
        <figcaption>Holding the cutterhead with a second Torx wrench during insert removal</figcaption>
      </div>

      <div class="warning">
        <strong>Knife inserts are dangerously sharp.</strong> Use extreme caution when inspecting, removing, or replacing. Turn off and disconnect power before any maintenance. Torque each screw to 52&ndash;60 in/lbs. Loose inserts can be propelled at high speed from a rotating cutterhead, causing injury.
      </div>

      <h3>Knife Rotation / Replacement</h3>
      <ol>
        <li>The knife inserts are four-sided. When dull, remove each knife, rotate 90&deg; for a fresh edge, and re-install. No further adjustment is necessary. Use a Torx wrench to remove the insert screw. Use a second Torx wrench in another screw to hold the cutterhead from rotating. <strong>Do not use your hand to hold the cutterhead.</strong></li>
        <li>It is advisable to rotate all inserts at the same time to maintain consistent cutting. However, if only one or more develop a nick, rotate only those affected. Each insert has an etched reference mark for tracking rotation.</li>
        <li><strong>Important:</strong> When removing or rotating inserts, clean sawdust from the screw, insert, and cutterhead platform. Dust accumulation can prevent proper seating and affect cut quality.</li>
        <li>Before installing each screw, lightly coat threads with machine oil and wipe off excess. Torque each screw to 52&ndash;60 in/lbs.</li>
      </ol>

      <h2>Fence Adjustments</h2>

      <h3>Fence Slide Position</h3>
      <p>The fence can be adjusted to use all or a portion of the cutterhead. Loosen the locking handle and turn the adjustment knob to position the fence.</p>
      <div class="figure">
        <img src="/manuals/laguna-jx8/p20_02.jpg" alt="Fence slide components — locking handle and adjustment knob" />
        <figcaption>Fence slide components</figcaption>
      </div>

      <h3>90-Degree Stop</h3>
      <p>The 90-degree position has an included reference stop. To adjust: flip the stop into position, loosen the lock nut, rotate the adjusting screw until the fence is at 90 degrees to the table, then tighten the lock nut. Verify with a square placed on the outfeed table against the fence.</p>

      <h3>Fence Tilt</h3>
      <p>To adjust the fence perpendicular or angled to the bed, loosen the locking lever and adjust to the desired position.</p>
      <div class="figure">
        <img src="/manuals/laguna-jx8/p21_00.jpg" alt="Fence stops and locks — 90-degree and 45-degree reference stops" />
        <figcaption>Fence stops and locks</figcaption>
      </div>

      <h3>Calibrating the Thickness Scale</h3>
      <div class="image-row">
        <img src="/manuals/laguna-jx8/p20_00.jpg" alt="Thickness scale on infeed table" />
        <img src="/manuals/laguna-jx8/p20_01.jpg" alt="Lock pin for thickness scale calibration" />
      </div>
      <ol>
        <li>Loosen the infeed table locking handle by rotating counterclockwise.</li>
        <li>Pull and hold the lock pin while positioning the handle to 1/64". Tighten the handle.</li>
        <li>Make a test cut halfway on sample material. Measure the depth of cut/stock removal.</li>
        <li>If not 1/64", adjust the red pointer by loosening the Phillips screw, adjusting, and retightening.</li>
      </ol>

      <h2>Operation</h2>

      <div class="warning">
        <strong>Use push blocks for face jointing!</strong> Do not place your hands near the cutterhead or guard. Place the jointer on a secure, stable surface and clamp or bolt it into position.
      </div>

      <h3>Basic Jointing Procedure</h3>
      <ol>
        <li>Establish the proper depth of cut (1/8" maximum). 1/64" is recommended for the best finish with least chance of kickback. Several shallow cuts generally provide a better finish than one deep cut.</li>
        <li>Start dust collection.</li>
        <li>Start the jointer.</li>
        <li>Feed stock into the cutterhead while maintaining contact on the bed and against the fence. Maintain a firm stance. Move hands along stock when feeding. Lift hands as they come near the cutterhead and reposition them on the outfeed side. <strong>Do not allow hands within 3 inches of the cutterhead.</strong></li>
        <li>Reposition to the outfeed side and control/support stock until past the cutterhead and the guard has fully closed.</li>
      </ol>

      <div class="note">
        The infeed table extension can be extended for support of long material. Loosen the two locking studs under the bed, pull the extension out, and tighten the studs.
      </div>

      <div class="image-row">
        <img src="/manuals/laguna-jx8/p22_01.jpg" alt="Edge jointing on the JX8" />
        <img src="/manuals/laguna-jx8/p22_02.jpg" alt="Face jointing on the JX8 with push blocks" />
      </div>

      <h3>Beveling</h3>
      <p>The fence can be adjusted up to 45 degrees toward or away from the infeed/outfeed tables. Angling the fence toward the tables reduces stock slippage and is a safer method when the application allows.</p>
      <div class="figure">
        <img src="/manuals/laguna-jx8/p22_03.jpg" alt="Beveling with fence angled toward tables" />
        <figcaption>Beveling with the fence tilted</figcaption>
      </div>

      <div class="note">
        The two 45-degree positions include reference stops. To adjust, loosen the lock nut and rotate the adjusting screw until the fence is at 45 degrees, angled in or out.
      </div>

      <h3>Rabbeting</h3>
      <p>Rabbeting is a groove along the edge of stock. Position the fence for the width of the rabbet cut (distance from the outermost knife insert edge to the fence). Set depth with the infeed table adjustment handle. Do not set deeper than 1/64" per pass; several passes may be required.</p>
      <div class="image-row">
        <img src="/manuals/laguna-jx8/p23_00.jpg" alt="Rabbeting setup on the JX8" />
        <img src="/manuals/laguna-jx8/p24_01.jpg" alt="Rabbeting cut in progress" />
      </div>

      <div class="danger">
        <strong>The spring-loaded guard (red) may need to be removed for rabbeting wide stock.</strong> Loosen the hex bolt and lift the guard with pin from the machine. Replace the guard as soon as the machine stops. Never allow hands near the cutterhead when the guard is removed.
      </div>

      <h2>Maintenance</h2>

      <h3>General</h3>
      <p>Keep the machine clean. Wood contains moisture, and sawdust left on surfaces will cause rust. Use only Teflon-based lubricant &mdash; regular oil attracts dust and dirt. Periodically check that all nuts and bolts are tight.</p>

      <h3>Daily Checks</h3>
      <ol>
        <li>Clean the machine and lubricate unpainted surfaces with Teflon lubricant. Wipe off excess and buff with a dry cloth to reduce rust and table friction.</li>
        <li>Check knife inserts for nicks and sharpness.</li>
        <li>Inspect for damage and loose or worn parts.</li>
      </ol>

      <h3>Weekly Checks</h3>
      <ol>
        <li>Clean the cutterhead. Do not touch knife inserts.</li>
        <li>Check knife inserts for nicks and sharpness.</li>
        <li>Inspect for damage and loose or worn parts.</li>
        <li>Check dust extraction for blockages.</li>
      </ol>

      <h3>Monthly Checks</h3>
      <ol>
        <li>Check the drive belt for wear, splits, and cuts.</li>
        <li>Clean the motor compartment and motor to ensure cooling fins work efficiently.</li>
        <li>Inspect for damage and loose or worn parts.</li>
      </ol>

      <h3>Outfeed Table Adjustment</h3>
      <p>The outfeed table is factory-adjusted to be level with (or up to max .006" lower than) the Top Dead Center of the knife inserts.</p>
      <ol>
        <li>Loosen the adjustment lock with an 8mm hex wrench (not included).</li>
        <li>Adjust the height with the outfeed table adjustment handle.</li>
        <li>Tighten the adjustment lock.</li>
      </ol>
      <div class="figure">
        <img src="/manuals/laguna-jx8/p27_01.jpg" alt="Outfeed table adjustment — lock and handle location" />
        <figcaption>Outfeed table adjustment</figcaption>
      </div>

      <h3>Drive Belt Adjustment</h3>
      <p>Proper tension: belt can be depressed approximately 1/2" midway between pulleys (1/4" from each side).</p>
      <ol>
        <li>Remove the four screws holding the back panel to the stand.</li>
        <li>Loosen the four motor mount bolts.</li>
        <li>Slide the motor downward to tension the belt.</li>
        <li>Tighten the four motor mounting bolts and replace the back cover.</li>
      </ol>
      <div class="image-row">
        <img src="/manuals/laguna-jx8/p27_02.jpg" alt="Motor mounting bolts for belt tension adjustment" />
        <img src="/manuals/laguna-jx8/p24_02.jpg" alt="Motor mount detail" />
      </div>

      <h3>Adjusting Tables Coplanar</h3>
      <p>The infeed and outfeed tables are precisely aligned at the factory, but misalignment can occur during shipping. The outfeed table must be parallel and flush with the cutterhead before adjusting the infeed table.</p>

      <h4>Coplanarity Test</h4>
      <ol>
        <li>Disconnect the machine from power.</li>
        <li>Remove the cutterhead guard by loosening the set screw(s).</li>
        <li>Slide the fence assembly back.</li>
        <li>Place a straight edge across both tables in multiple positions. The straight edge should rest flat and flush with both tables (not on an insert knife). If not, follow the adjustment steps below.</li>
      </ol>

      <h4>Outfeed Table &mdash; Parallel to Cutterhead</h4>
      <ol>
        <li>Disconnect power, remove cutterhead guard, push fence back, remove rear access panel.</li>
        <li>Place a straight edge on the outfeed table halfway over the cutterhead. Rotate the drive belt to bring an insert knife to top-dead-center.</li>
        <li>Loosen the screw lock to release the outfeed table adjustment lever.</li>
        <li>Loosen the cap screw on the back of the adjustment lever and lower the outfeed table until the straight edge is level with the top-dead-center of the knife inserts.</li>
        <li>Place a straight edge in multiple positions to verify the outfeed table is parallel with the cutterhead.</li>
        <li>If not parallel, loosen the set screws for the eccentric bushings and rotate them to adjust. Tighten set screws.</li>
        <li>Confirm the outfeed table is flush with the cutterhead at TDC. Tighten the lock.</li>
      </ol>
      <div class="image-row">
        <img src="/manuals/laguna-jx8/p28_03.jpg" alt="Checking outfeed table with straight edge" />
        <img src="/manuals/laguna-jx8/p29_00.jpg" alt="Screw lock and outfeed table adjustment lever" />
      </div>
      <div class="image-row">
        <img src="/manuals/laguna-jx8/p29_01.png" alt="Cap screw on back of outfeed table adjustment" />
        <img src="/manuals/laguna-jx8/p29_02.jpg" alt="Back view of outfeed table adjustment" />
      </div>

      <h4>Infeed Table &mdash; Parallel to Outfeed Table</h4>
      <ol>
        <li>Confirm the outfeed table is parallel and flush with insert tips at top-dead-center.</li>
        <li>Place a straight edge across both infeed and outfeed tables. If inserts interfere, rotate the cutterhead.</li>
        <li>Check in multiple positions.</li>
        <li>If the straight edge lies uniformly flat against both tables in all positions, re-install fence, blade guard, and rear access panel.</li>
        <li>If not, adjust the eccentric bushings under the infeed table by removing the depth stop release knob and infeed table cover.</li>
      </ol>
      <div class="image-row">
        <img src="/manuals/laguna-jx8/p30_00.jpg" alt="Eccentric bushings, cap screws, and set screws" />
        <img src="/manuals/laguna-jx8/p30_01.jpg" alt="Checking bed alignment with straight edge" />
      </div>

      <h4>Table Parallelism Adjustment</h4>
      <p>This adjustment needs to be done very precisely and typically does not require re-adjustment once set.</p>
      <ol>
        <li>Place a straight edge on the outfeed table over the cutterhead, slightly touching the cutterhead body.</li>
        <li>Remove plugs and loosen cap screws to release and remove the outfeed table cover.</li>
        <li>Loosen set screws for the eccentric bushings.</li>
        <li>Adjust eccentric bushings until the straight edge slightly touches the insert knife at TDC at each position.</li>
        <li>Verify parallelism, ensure eccentric collars are seated snugly, and tighten cap screws then set screws.</li>
        <li>For infeed table: remove the depth stop release knob and infeed table cover, loosen set screws, and adjust eccentric bushings similarly.</li>
        <li>Verify parallelism in all positions. Tighten cap screws and set screws.</li>
        <li>Re-install table covers and the infeed table depth stop release knob.</li>
      </ol>
      <div class="image-row">
        <img src="/manuals/laguna-jx8/p30_05.jpg" alt="Straight edge verification of table parallelism" />
        <img src="/manuals/laguna-jx8/p32_00.jpg" alt="Checking table alignment at multiple positions" />
        <img src="/manuals/laguna-jx8/p32_02.jpg" alt="Eccentric bushings detail" />
      </div>

      <div class="note">
        Confirm the eccentric bushings are fully seated (hex collar pushed snug into bracket) and cap screws are tight before tightening set screws. This prevents excessive play and side-to-side bed movement.
      </div>

      <h3>Dust Collection</h3>
      <p>To ensure proper operation and longest knife life, maintain full air flow to your dust collection system. Keep the filter media clean and verify there are no obstructions in the ducting or hoses.</p>

